Package com.mitsuki.jmatrix.enums

Enum JMErrorCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<JMErrorCode>
      • com.mitsuki.jmatrix.enums.JMErrorCode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<JMErrorCode>
    public enum JMErrorCode
extends Enum<JMErrorCode>
    The JMErrorCode enum represents error codes for various error conditions that can occur within a JMatrix library. Each error code is associated with an integer error number, a string representation of the error code, and a descriptive error message.

    This enum provides methods to retrieve the error number, error code, and error message. Additionally, it provides a static method to convert an error number or a string representation of the error code back to its corresponding JMErrorCode enum value, it is declared as valueOf(Object). The method does not throws an error if the type of value is unrecognized, instead it returns null.

    Example usage: 

     
   JMErrorCode errorCode = JMErrorCode.INVIDX;
   int errno = errorCode.getErrno();        // 201
   String errcode = errorCode.getCode();    // INVIDX
   String errmsg = errorCode.getMessage();  // Given index is out bounds

    Get the error code from a thrown exception: 

     
   try {
      Matrix m = new Matrix();
      m = Matrix.mult(m, 5);
   } catch (Exception e) {
      if (e instanceof JMatrixBaseException) {
          e = (JMatrixBaseException) e;
          String errcode = e.getErrorCode().getCode();  // NULLMT
      }
   }

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • INVIDX

        public static final JMErrorCode INVIDX
        Error code indicating that the given index is out of bounds.

        This error code is useful to indicates that user gives an index either of row or column (which from methods that indexing-related, such as Matrix.insertRow(int, double[]), Matrix.dropColumn(int), and Matrix.display(int)).

        Error number: 201

        Related exception: InvalidIndexException

      • INVTYP

        public static final JMErrorCode INVTYP
        Error code indicating that the matrix has an invalid type.

        This error code will be in the IllegalMatrixSizeException exception which related to invalid type of matrix. For example, user attempting to calculate trace with a 5x3 matrix, which is an illegal attemption because trace calculation are only for square matrices.

        Error number: 202

        Related exception: IllegalMatrixSizeException

      • NULLMT

        public static final JMErrorCode NULLMT
        Error code indicating that the matrix is null or the matrix entries is null.

        A matrix with null entries can be constructed using Matrix() constructor, which is not require any arguments. Thus, the returned matrix is a matrix with a null entries (in other words, an uninitialized matrix).

        Error number: 203

        Related exception: NullMatrixException

      • UNKERR

        public static final JMErrorCode UNKERR
        Error code indicating an unknown error.

        This error code can be made by the JMatrixBaseException class when failed to evaluate the given error number (errno) or the cause exception is not an instance of that class while trying to get the error code from the given cause exception, and ended up constructs with this error code.

        Error number: 400

        Related exception: JMatrixBaseException
